urlText: Opal can be used between Wollongong and Moss Vale, Exeter and Bundanoon stations.
content:
If travelling by Coach between Wollongong station and Moss Vale, Exeter or Bundanoon stations you can use your Opal card or contactless card or device to tap on or off at your origin/destination station provided the origin/destination is an Opal enabled station.

If travelling onto Goulburn, or other Opal enabled station along the Southern Highlands Line, you should not tap off when transferring from Coach to an Intercity train but instead tap off at your destination station.

Booking is not required for Opal customers on this route.
subtitle: Opal can be used between Wollongong and Moss Vale, Exeter and Bundanoon stations.

urlText: Opal can be used between Bathurst and Lithgow Stations when booked
content: If travelling by Coach to or from Bathurst you can use your Opal card or contactless card or device to tap on or off at Bathurst station and your origin/destination station provided the origin/destination is an Opal enabled station. When using Opal you will need to reserve a seat, at no cost, through the Contact Centre by calling 13 22 32 (Between 07:00 to 22:00 each day).
subtitle: Opal can be used between Bathurst and Lithgow Stations when booked

urlText: Additional bus service and service changes from 24 January
content:
From 24 January, bus services will be added as part of network changes. The changes to services include:
  • More than 700 additional bus services for Sydney’s North West and parts of the Lower North Shore.
  • Two new all-day frequent services operating every 10 minutes, seven days a week between both West Ryde and Chatswood and the city.
To support the introduction of new services, there will be some bus route and timetable adjustments to existing services. Some routes are being replaced by new routes or extra services on other routes.

Find out more.

content:

To access Pitt Street or Eddy Avenue from the Grand Concourse or L1 light rail stop, please exit the station via the Western Forecourt or Northern Concourse.
